talk everything out?

116
00:09:06,540 --> 00:09:07,580
No way.

117
00:09:07,980 --> 00:09:09,340
You still won’t quit?

118
00:09:10,020 --> 00:09:11,540
I can’t, I can’t let it go.

119
00:09:11,620 --> 00:09:13,580
I just want a result.

120
00:09:24,620 --> 00:09:25,220
Hello?

121
00:09:26,860 --> 00:09:27,500
Buzui.

122
00:09:35,820 --> 00:09:36,420
Beidao.

123
00:09:36,820 --> 00:09:38,380
Beidao, help!

124
00:09:38,900 --> 00:09:39,460
Get lost!

125
00:09:42,260 --> 00:09:42,780
Beidao,

126
00:09:42,980 --> 00:09:44,240
my sister is in danger.

127
00:09:49,740 --> 00:09:50,340
Speak.

128
00:09:51,940 --> 00:09:53,700
If I can’t pay off my debts,

129
00:09:54,260 --> 00:09:55,660
they will take my sister.

130
00:09:56,340 --> 00:09:57,700
Don’t you dare lie to me!

131
00:09:57,820 --> 00:09:58,460
I swear

132
00:09:58,580 --> 00:09:59,940
I’m telling the truth.

133
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:01,830
Who's the creditor?

134
00:10:03,260 --> 00:10:04,620
Some loan shark.

135
00:10:04,820 --> 00:10:06,620
What’s it to do with your sister?

136
00:10:06,940 --> 00:10:08,060
If they can’t catch me,

137
00:10:08,060 --> 00:10:09,780
they’ll go after my sister.

138
00:10:11,460 --> 00:10:12,860
Does she know about this?

139
00:10:13,380 --> 00:10:14,340
Not yet.

140
00:10:14,460 --> 00:10:15,980
That’s why she’s in danger.

141
00:10:15,980 --> 00:10:18,040
They say they’ll take her away today.

142
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:21,320
Bring me to see the loan shark.

143
00:10:22,060 --> 00:10:22,660
Let's go.

144
00:10:37,900 --> 00:10:39,100
You have company.

145
00:10:40,740 --> 00:10:41,300
So,

146
00:10:41,420 --> 00:10:43,540
is he gonna pay for you?

147
00:10:43,660 --> 00:10:44,540
No money.

148
00:10:46,020 --> 00:10:47,340
Then why are you here?

149
00:10:47,420 --> 00:10:48,340
To mess with me?

150
00:10:52,300 --> 00:10:54,540
Why did he borrow money from you?

151
00:10:54,660 --> 00:10:55,900
Why?

152
00:10:56,180 --> 00:10:57,180
To gamble.

153
00:10:57,220 --> 00:10:58,260
Who owns the casino?

154
00:10:58,260 --> 00:10:58,860
He owns it.

155
00:10:59,060 --> 00:10:59,620
It’s...

156
00:10:59,740 --> 00:11:00,900
It’s mine. So what?

157
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:06,100
So he lost money to you,

158
00:11:06,540 --> 00:11:08,070
and then borrowed from you.

159
00:11:08,140 --> 00:11:10,860
If he can’t pay you back, you’ll take his sister.

160
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:16,140
You came here just to tell me nonsense?

161
00:11:16,860 --> 00:11:17,700
Pay up.

162
00:11:18,180 --> 00:11:18,820
No.

163
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:21,060
Guys,

164
00:11:21,140 --> 00:11:21,860
kick him out.

165
00:11:21,860 --> 00:11:22,720
Leave him here.

166
00:11:56,260 --> 00:11:57,580
How dare you touch me!

167
00:12:15,620 --> 00:12:16,780
Nice move.

168
00:12:19,860 --> 00:12:20,590
The IOU note.

169
00:12:22,740 --> 00:12:23,500
I don’t have it.

170
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:24,220
Give me.

171
00:12:24,340 --> 00:12:25,580
Here, here, here.

172
00:12:29,380 --> 00:12:29,940
Beidao,

173
00:12:30,100 --> 00:12:31,300
that was impressive.

174
00:12:31,340 --> 00:12:33,380
Your moves were too fast for me to see clearly.

175
00:12:33,380 --> 00:12:33,860
Hey,

176
00:12:34,220 --> 00:12:35,900
you know kung fu?

177
00:12:38,420 --> 00:12:39,420
Where’s the note?

178
00:12:39,660 --> 00:12:40,460
This?

179
00:12:40,660 --> 00:12:41,660
I’ll tear it up.

180
00:12:43,300 --> 00:12:44,660
Now, you owe me.

181
00:12:45,420 --> 00:12:46,020
What?

182
00:12:46,140 --> 00:12:46,860
Beidao,

183
00:12:46,980 --> 00:12:48,220
we’re family.

184
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:49,660
If my sister knows...

185
00:12:49,660 --> 00:12:50,990
Don’t bother her again.

186
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:51,540
What?

187
00:12:51,980 --> 00:12:52,900
Come to me.

188
00:12:56,540 --> 00:12:57,180
Beidao...

189
00:13:20,140 --> 00:13:21,200
Sorry for the wait.

190
00:13:22,340 --> 00:13:22,940
It’s OK.

191
00:13:23,140 --> 00:13:24,060
I just arrived.

192
00:13:29,380 --> 00:13:30,180
What’s wrong?

193
00:13:32,020 --> 00:13:32,860
Nothing.

194
00:13:34,580 --> 00:13:35,460
Mi Ya,

195
00:13:36,340 --> 00:13:38,660
you asked me out...

196
00:13:38,660 --> 00:13:39,460
For Yi Beidao.

197
00:13:43,060 --> 00:13:45,700
There are certain things you need to know.

198
00:13:47,940 --> 00:13:49,580
The man who came back

199
00:13:49,860 --> 00:13:51,180
isn’t Yi Beidao.

200
00:13:51,780 --> 00:13:52,900
He’s Yi Nanke,

201
00:13:53,100 --> 00:13:54,700
Yi Beidao’s twin brother.

202
00:13:57,260 --> 00:13:58,620
Twin brother?

203
00:14:02,620 --> 00:14:03,740
Impossible.

204
00:14:04,140 --> 00:14:05,820
I never heard about him.

205
00:14:06,380 --> 00:14:08,020
- Back in high school...  - In high school,

206
00:14:08,020 --> 00:14:09,820
they shared one identity.

207
00:14:12,260 --> 00:14:13,180
Why?

208
00:14:14,340 --> 00:14:16,200
After their father went missing,

209
00:14:16,220 --> 00:14:18,950
they couldn’t afford to pay for their education.

210
00:14:21,860 --> 00:14:22,820
Yi Nanke

211
00:14:22,820 --> 00:14:25,350
blamed your father for everything happened.

212
00:14:27,300 --> 00:14:29,580
My...my father?

213
00:14:33,100 --> 00:14:34,260
That’s impossible.

214
00:14:45,700 --> 00:14:46,900
What did you think of?

215
00:14:49,420 --> 00:14:50,700
Yi Beidao.

216
00:14:52,020 --> 00:14:53,380
Yi Nanke.

217
00:14:54,380 --> 00:14:54,940
Buzui,

218
00:14:56,100 --> 00:14:57,060
who is this?

219
00:14:58,460 --> 00:14:59,740
Mr. Yi.

220
00:15:00,460 --> 00:15:01,060
Mi...

221
00:15:02,980 --> 00:15:04,020
Missing.

222
00:15:04,860 --> 00:15:07,060
The deputy manager of my father’s winery,

223
00:15:07,060 --> 00:15:08,580
that missing man.

224
00:15:16,620 --> 00:15:18,020
So that’s what happened.

225
00:15:19,300 --> 00:15:21,180
I actually met

226
00:15:22,300 --> 00:15:23,820
two persons back then?

227
00:15:26,980 --> 00:15:28,100
Where’s Yi Beidao?

228
00:15:30,940 --> 00:15:33,700
Where is he?

229
00:15:35,020 --> 00:15:36,480
He passed away 7 years ago.

230
00:15:42,180 --> 00:15:43,380
He died?

231
00:15:46,940 --> 00:15:48,500
What happened back then?

232
00:15:48,820 --> 00:15:51,020
It’s not like what Yi Nanke said, right?

233
00:15:54,340 --> 00:15:55,100
Buzui,

234
00:15:56,060 --> 00:15:57,900
I want you to talk to Yi Beidao.

235
00:16:00,060 --> 00:16:02,140
He and you mean the most to Yi Beidao.

236
00:16:02,420 --> 00:16:03,700
I’m sure he doesn’t want to

237
00:16:03,700 --> 00:16:04,700
see you like this.

238
00:16:10,420 --> 00:16:11,540
He hates me.

239
00:16:12,420 --> 00:16:14,060
He’d rather see me gone.

240
00:16:16,380 --> 00:16:17,780
There’s nothing I can do.

241
00:16:18,940 --> 00:16:20,140
You should at least know

242
00:16:20,140 --> 00:16:21,460
what really happened.

243
00:16:51,420 --> 00:16:52,220
You’re back.

244
00:16:53,220 --> 00:16:53,700
Dad.

245
00:16:54,860 --> 00:16:56,380
You don’t look well.

246
00:16:58,220 --> 00:16:59,220
You must be tired.

247
00:17:00,580 --> 00:17:02,580
I had a lot of work.

248
00:17:02,980 --> 00:17:04,619
Here, have an apple.

249
00:17:04,619 --> 00:17:05,060
Here.

250
00:17:05,180 --> 00:17:06,660
I just peeled it.

251
00:17:08,260 --> 00:17:09,190
Open your mouth.

252
00:17:12,900 --> 00:17:14,660
You look skinny recently.

253
00:17:15,619 --> 00:17:16,220
Do I?

254
00:17:17,099 --> 00:17:17,579
Here.

255
00:17:18,460 --> 00:17:19,260
One more.

256
00:17:21,579 --> 00:17:22,780
What do you want for dinner?

257
00:17:22,780 --> 00:17:23,780
I’ll cook for you.

258
00:17:23,819 --> 00:17:24,380
Dad,

259
00:17:24,540 --> 00:17:25,619
